        <headline>Beach Hazards Statement issued April 2 at 3:48PM CDT until April 4 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...High risk of rip currents and minor coastal flooding,
mainly during times of high tides expected.

* WHERE...Gulf-facing beaches, including the Matagorda
Peninsula, Brazoria County beaches, Galveston Island and the
Bolivar Peninsula.

* WHEN...Through late Thursday night.

* IMPACTS...Rip currents can sweep even the best swimmers away
from shore into deeper water. Elevated tides could lead to minor
flooding of beaches, lots, parks, and roads with only isolated road
closures possible. This includes the lowest more-prone spots like
HWY 87/124 along the Bolivar Peninsula, Western Galveston Island,
Bluewater Highway and Surfside.
</description>
        <instruction>Remain out of the water to avoid hazardous swimming conditions.</instruction>
